; Fixture for the booking-failure partition regression: a transaction
; with an explicit cost spec that has no matching lot. Booking fails
; on this txn with NoMatchingLot. The loader should partition it out
; before late-phase validation, so the user sees ONLY the BOOK error
; — no cascading TransactionUnbalanced or follow-on validation noise.
;
; The auto_tag plugin runs after booking and round-trips every txn
; through the wrapper protocol (which doesn't preserve byte spans).
; Pre-partition this scenario broke `failed_bookings` lookup because
; the post-plugin span no longer matched what was recorded at booking
; time. Partition sidesteps the issue entirely.

option "operating_currency" "USD"
plugin "auto_tag" "{}"

2024-01-01 open Assets:Stock STOCK
2024-01-01 open Assets:Cash USD

2024-02-01 * "buy lot"
  Assets:Stock   10 STOCK {1.00 USD}
  Assets:Cash  -10.00 USD

; Booking fails: no lot at 999.99 USD exists.
2024-03-01 * "sell from nonexistent lot"
  Assets:Stock   -5 STOCK {999.99 USD}
  Assets:Cash     5.00 USD

; A subsequent legitimate txn that should NOT cascade errors. Without
; partition, the failed txn above stays in the directive list with
; unresolved cost on its remaining 5 STOCK lot reduction, and Late
; phase tries to reduce it from the validator's separate inventory
; state — which never received the failed reduction — emitting
; misleading NoMatchingLot/InsufficientUnits errors here.
2024-04-01 * "legitimate sell from remaining lot"
  Assets:Stock   -5 STOCK {1.00 USD}
  Assets:Cash     5.00 USD
